OL,7,FAfter six months, the conch-blowing
OL,8,Fgroup showed a 34% reduction in
OL,9,Fdaytime sleepiness, improved sleep
OL,10,Fquality scores, and four to five fewer
OL,11,Fapnoea events per hour of sleep. Their
OL,12,Fnighttime oxygen levels rose by an
OL,13,Faverage of 7%, and their neck
OL,14,Fcircumference decreased, suggesting
OL,15,Fstructural changes in the airway.
OL,17,FBy contrast, the control group saw no
OL,18,Fsignificant improvements - and in some
OL,19,Fcases, slightly worsened readings.
