OL,7,FConch blowing involves deep inhalation
OL,8,Ffollowed by forceful exhalation
OL,9,Fthrough the shell's narrow opening,
OL,10,Fproducing a resonant sound. This
OL,11,Faction engages the diaphragm,
OL,12,Fintercostal muscles, and upper airway
OL,13,Fmuscles, providing resistance training
OL,14,Ffor the respiratory system.
OL,16,FResearchers believe this muscle
OL,17,Fengagement helps prevent airway
OL,18,Fcollapse during sleep, which is the
OL,19,Fhallmark of OSA.
